{
  "stem": "11611.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, it was a very hectic period for me because although I was about 60 years old at that point, I'd gotten back to a schedule which I didn't like, which is about 60 to 70 hours a week.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I would spend two, three hours a day at Arnold and Porter, either early in the morning or late at night.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And during the time, I remember-- and then I would spend the rest of the time at OSI.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was probably spending, oh, 2/3 of the time at OSI, which was why I renegotiated my deal with the firm.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I remember at one point working regularly at OSI, and at night, I would fly to New York and negotiate a contract for the sale of a business of one of our major clients, a major insurance company.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For Arnold and Porter.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had this dual role.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- I would have two sets of secretaries.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had one secretary, at least part time, at OSI.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then I had my regular secretary at my office at Arnold and Porter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was taking taxicabs back and forth, every day of the week.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I never had any doubts as to the virtues of the Nuremberg Trials.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think, unfortunately, that they are still significant, but more symbolically significant than as controlling rules of conduct.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- the cases established several principles, one of which was that you could set up an international court to try violations of international criminal law.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A second was the defense that only states and not individuals are the subject of international law failed at Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
